## What now?

This document covers Dusk's basic functionalities. You can try a few things in
the interpreter, but you are hungry for more. What to read next?

* Take a look at doc/dict to have an idea of available base words.
* doc/sys/io is central to many, many things in Dusk.
* doc/sys/file lets you play with the filesystem.
* doc/lib/alloc covers dynamic memory allocation.
* doc/hal covers the HAL on which the coolest Dusk features rely.
* doc/cc covers Dusk's central feature: its C compiler.
* doc/text/ed to edit text files.
* doc/code explains how to grok Dusk's code.

There are many more subjects covered by this documentation, but these listed
above should be read first. As for the rest, I'll let you browse.
